Aberdeen Asset Management

From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia


					Jump to:					navigation, 					search


Aberdeen Asset Management





Type

Public (LSE: ADN)


Industry
Investment Management


Founded
1983; 34 years ago (1983)


Headquarters
Aberdeen, Scotland, UK



Key people

Simon Troughton
(Chairman)
Martin Gilbert
(CEO)
Hugh Young
(Head of Investments)
Bev Hendry
(Chief Executive - Head of Americas)


Products
Equities, Fixed Income and Property asset classes


Revenue
